    "plan_content": "## Plan: Ollama Model Rename Feature\n\nHere's the full implementation plan across **4 files** and **7 precise insertion points**:\n\n---\n\n### Why it works this way\n\nThe key insight for rename vs. copy+delete is that **blob layers must not be deleted** — only the source manifest file is removed. `(*Manifest).RemoveLayers()` checks all other manifests before removing blobs, so calling it right after `CopyModel` would still be safe, but skipping it entirely is cleaner and avoids unnecessary I/O. `(*Manifest).Remove()` handles only the manifest file and empty-dir cleanup.\n\n---\n\n### Step 1 — `api/types.go` (after line 765, after `CopyRequest`)\nAdd `RenameRequest` with the same `Source`/`Destination` shape as `CopyRequest`.\n\n### Step 2 — `api/client.go` (after line 387, after `Copy`)\nAdd `Rename(ctx, *RenameRequest) error` that calls `c.do(ctx, http.MethodPost, \"/api/rename\", req, nil)`.\n\n### Step 3 — `server/routes.go` (after line 1698)\nRegister `r.POST(\"/api/rename\", s.RenameHandler)`.\n\n### Step 4 — `server/routes.go` (after line 1483, after `CopyHandler`)\nAdd `RenameHandler` with this flow:\n1. Bind JSON → 400 on bad/missing body\n2. `model.ParseName(r.Source)` + `getExistingName` → 400 if invalid\n3. `manifest.ParseNamedManifest(src)` → **404** if `os.IsNotExist`\n4. `model.ParseName(r.Destination)` + `getExistingName` → 400 if invalid\n5. `manifest.ParseNamedManifest(dst)` with no error → **409** (destination exists)\n6. `CopyModel(src, dst)` → copies the manifest file\n7. `srcManifest.Remove()` → removes **only** the source manifest (no `RemoveLayers`)\n\n### Step 5 — `cmd/cmd.go` (after line 1350, after `CopyHandler`)\nAdd `RenameHandler` that builds `api.RenameRequest{args[0], args[1]}`, calls `client.Rename(...)`, prints `\"renamed '%s' to '%s'\\n\"`.\n\n### Step 6 — `cmd/cmd.go` (after line 2263, after `copyCmd`)\nAdd `renameCmd` with `Use: \"rename SOURCE DESTINATION\"`, `Args: cobra.ExactArgs(2)`, `PreRunE: checkServerHeartbeat`, `RunE: RenameHandler`.\n\n### Step 7 — `cmd/cmd.go` (two `AddCommand` sites ~lines 2298 and 2345)\nAdd `renameCmd` adjacent to `copyCmd` in both places.",
